senses.sense_definition: A leaf, often of tissue paper or other thin paper, inserted between the pages of a book to protect illustrations.

examples.text: The antique book contains a tissue <w>interleaf</w> before every engraving.
Please handle the protective <w>interleaf</w> gently to avoid tearing the paper.

senses.sense_definition: A sheet of paper or cardboard, placed between layers on a pallet to create a cohesive structure.

examples.text: We need a cardboard <w>interleaf</w> to stabilize the pallet load.
The warehouse uses a plastic <w>interleaf</w> between heavy metal sheets.

senses.sense_definition: To insert blank leaves or sheets between the pages of a book or layers of a stack.

examples.text: You should <w>interleaf</w> the document with blank sheets for comments.
The printer can <w>interleaf</w> colored paper between the white pages.
